  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddClass
    Activity that allows the student to add a class by inputting a given code that is the class's id in the database.
    Admin
    This is the Admin user which is a person who has complete control of the system, probably a principal or dean.
    AdminAddClass
    Activity that allows the student to add a class by inputting a given code that is the class's id in the database.
    AdminAddUser
    Activity that allows the student to add a class by inputting a given code that is the class's id in the database.
    AdminSearchView
    Shows list of whatever the admin happens to be searching for.
    AdminSearchViewCustomGrid
    Tells the grid that is displayed in AdminSearchView how it is to be laid out.
    AdminViewActivity
    Is the homepage for the admin user.
    AttendanceCard
    The attendance card which shows all the attendance of the students for a given day.
    AttendanceCustomGrid
    Sets up the custom grid for the attendance objects of all the dates for a given class.
    AttendanceStudentCustomGrid
    Sets up the custom grid for the attendance of every student for a given date and class.
    AttendanceViewer
    Is the viewer that shows a list of attendance objects for every date of a given class.
    ChangeCourseInfo
    Class used by the teacher and admin users to change the description of a course.
    ChatActivity
    Activity for chatting with your class
    ClassCustomGrid
    A grid manager for the attendance checkin at the home fragment of the StudentViewActivity.
    ClassInfoActivity
    Activity that shows the class's info
    ClassInfoActivityTest
    Unit tests for the ClassInfoActivity that mocks Intent.
    Course
    Class for a Course object
    CustomGrid
    The custom grid manager of the dashboard fragment for the classes that a user is assigned to
    DashboardFragment
    The fragment that displays the class dashboard of the StudentViewActivity and the TeacherViewActivity.
    ExampleInstrumentedTest
    Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
    ExampleUnitTest
    Example local unit test, which will execute on the development machine (host).
    HomeFragment
    The fragment that is the first thing users see.
    LocationUpdate
    Class that gets and updates the location of users
    LoginActivity
    A login screen that offers login via email/password.
    LoginActivityTest
    Tests the login activity
    MessageCustomGrid
    Tells the grid that is displayed in the notification fragment how it is to be laid out.
    NotificationsFragment
    The notification fragment of the StudentView and TeacherView activities.
    PasswordReset
    Resets the user's password
    PasswordResetTest
    Tests the password reset activity
    Stopwatch
    Stopwatch to keep track of time
    Student
    Student user
    StudentViewActivity
    Student's version of the app
    StudentViewActivityTest

    Teacher
    Class for the teacher user
    TeacherHome

    TeacherViewActivity
    Teacher's side of the app
    TeacherViewActivityTest

    User
    User class, used to create teachers and students
    UserInfoActivity
